abstract: >
  DTQEM (Dual‑Time Quantum Entanglement Model) provides a numerical and analytical framework
  for simulating open quantum systems under the Time‑Sovereignty hypothesis.
  Version 14.0 adds two exact analytical results:
  (1) Wave‑particle balance condition for pure dephasing:
      γφ₀·t_obs = 2 ln(tan θ), θ > 45°.
  (2) Resonance collapse from the maximally coherent state |+⟩:
      t_collapse = -ln(ε)/(2γ)  or  γ·t_collapse = -ln(ε)/2.
  Validated applications include:
  Davisson–Germer diffraction, quantum tunneling (Zeno effect, entropy ln 2), and Schottky emission.
  All Lindblad simulations use Liouvillian exponentiation (expm) reaching machine precision (errors < 1e-12).
  BLP measure = 0 confirms Markovianity. Limitations are documented (Gouanère experiment, no negative time).
  The code is open source with interactive GUIs, unit tests, and full documentation.
